The paper deals with information decomposition, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, based on the abstract and the terminology used, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
